headline: Stocks slip, Onsemi pulls Allegro offer, Palantir rises on NATO deal
summary: US stocks (^GSPC, ^IXIC, ^DJI)  slipped late in afternoon trading. Market Domination host Josh Lipton highlights chipmaker Onsemi’s (ON) decision to terminate its acquisition attempt of Allegro Microsystems (ALGM). Palantir (PLTR) shares climbed for a second straight day after NATO adopted its Maven smart system. Meanwhile, Applied Digital's (APLD) stock dropped following disappointing third quarter results. Stay up to date on the latest market action, minute-by-minute, with Yahoo Finance's Market Minute.
